; StartBridge - start the AmigaBridge daemon in TCP mode (port 2345).
;
; Manual run:   Execute DH0:AmigaBridge/StartBridge
; Auto-start:   add that same line to the END of S:User-Startup so the
;               bridge launches on every boot.
;
; Edit the path / port on the "Run" line below if you copied the daemon
; somewhere other than DH0:AmigaBridge, or want a different TCP port.
;
Echo "AmigaBridge: waiting a moment for the TCP/IP stack..."
Wait 3
Echo "AmigaBridge: starting TCP server on port 2345"
Run >NIL: DH0:AmigaBridge/amiga-bridge TCP 2345
Echo "AmigaBridge: launched - see its status window."
